      <h2 data-aos="fade-up">What is a Rehearsal Dinner?</h2>
      <p data-aos="fade-up">The Rehearsal Dinner is an intimate and elegant gathering, traditionally held the night before the wedding. It’s an opportunity for the couple to relax with close family and friends after the wedding rehearsal, sharing stories, laughter, and a beautiful meal together before the big day arrives.</p>
      
      <h2 data-aos="fade-up">Who Attends?</h2>
      <p data-aos="fade-up">This exclusive dinner is reserved for the bride and groom’s closest circle—immediate family, the bridal party, and selected out-of-town guests. It’s a moment to connect personally with those dearest to you before the grandeur of the wedding day.</p>
      
      <h2 data-aos="fade-up">Atmosphere & Style</h2>
      <p data-aos="fade-up">Whether hosted at a fine dining venue, a scenic vineyard, or a candlelit garden, the Rehearsal Dinner embodies elegance. With custom menus, meaningful toasts, and refined decor, the evening sets the tone for the celebration ahead.</p>
      
      <h2 data-aos="fade-up">Key Elements</h2>
      <ul>
        <li data-aos="fade-right"><strong>Venue:</strong> Private dining rooms, estates, rooftop restaurants, or family homes with style</li>
        <li data-aos="fade-left"><strong>Décor:</strong> Florals, soft lighting, personalized name cards, and luxurious table settings</li>
        <li data-aos="fade-right"><strong>Toasts:</strong> Heartfelt speeches by family, best man, or maid of honor</li>
        <li data-aos="fade-left"><strong>Menu:</strong> A thoughtfully curated dining experience with wine pairings</li>
        <li data-aos="fade-right"><strong>Gifts:</strong> Optional token gifts for the wedding party or parents</li>
      </ul>

    
